Above code snippet is from YARN-2003 which is handing changes in RM and Events for priority. When an app is submitted w/o priority, we would like to fill in with default priority from queue.

bq.why would we want to limit which priorities are running within a queue?
queueA: default=low 
queueB: default=medium

The type of apps which we run may vary from queueA to B. So by keeping default priority different for each queue will help to handle such case. Assume more high level apps are running in queueA often, and medium level in queueB. Making different default priority can help here.

[~leftnoteasy] Do you mean a global max priority which can help to limit the number associated with a priority ?

bq. we just cap it by max-priority-limit instead of throw exception? 
Yes. I will update this part as against throwing exception.

